===Noun===
'''favor'''

# A piece of help.
# A small gift; a [[party favor]].

====Derived terms====
*[[party favor]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To look upon [[fond]]ly; to [[prefer]].
#* And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail, thou that art highly favored, the Lord is with thee: blessed art thou among women. &mdash;[[Wikisource:Bible, English, King_James, Luke#Chapter 1|Luke 1:28]], King James version, 1611
# {{transitive}} To do a favor (noun sense 1) for; to show [[beneficence]] toward.
#: ''Would you favor us with a poetry reading?''

